headline: Coca-Cola and PepsiCo May Look Alike. Why They Don’t Trade Alike.
summary: Coke is primarily a beverage company with a big international footprint. Pepsi is a soda and snack giant, mostly in the U.S. In a year of tariff fears and weight-loss drugs, that’s a problem.
